### Import Better Auth Module in NestJS Root Module

Source: https://github.com/better-auth/better-auth/blob/canary/docs/content/docs/integrations/nestjs.mdx

Integrate Better Auth into your NestJS application by importing the `AuthModule` into your root module, typically `AppModule`. Use `AuthModule.forRoot()` to initialize it with your Better Auth instance, making authentication services available throughout your application.

```ts
import { Module } from '@nestjs/common';
import { AuthModule } from '@thallesp/nestjs-better-auth';
import { auth } from "./auth"; // Your Better Auth instance

@Module({
  imports: [
    AuthModule.forRoot({ auth }),
  ],
})
export class AppModule {}
```

