### Configure Better Auth Handler with Elysia Framework

Source: https://github.com/better-auth/better-auth/blob/canary/docs/content/docs/installation.mdx

This Elysia.js snippet defines a `betterAuthView` middleware that validates request methods (`GET`, `POST`) and forwards them to the `auth.handler`. It then mounts this middleware to `/api/auth/*` and starts the Elysia server, providing authentication integration for Elysia applications.

```typescript
import { Elysia, Context } from "elysia";
import { auth } from "./auth";

const betterAuthView = (context: Context) => {
    const BETTER_AUTH_ACCEPT_METHODS = ["POST", "GET"]
    // validate request method
    if(BETTER_AUTH_ACCEPT_METHODS.includes(context.request.method)) {
        return auth.handler(context.request);
    } else {
        context.error(405)
    }
}

const app = new Elysia().all("/api/auth/*", betterAuthView).listen(3000);

console.log(
`ðŸ¦Š Elysia is running at ${app.server?.hostname}:${app.server?.port}`
);
```

